<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-01-0699 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a plant for the recovery of energy from waste gases from boilers, theseare simultaneously taken for cleaning via a heat exchanger to heat heatingwater or service water and are taken to a conventional gas chimney consistingof a galvanized sheet metal pipe, where the condensate extracted fromthe stack gas washer is neutralized in a device, so that the cleanedand neutralized condensate can be taken as washing liquid for the stackgas washer and/or directly to an existing waste water system, withoutcausing any damage to the environment.</TEXT></DOC>